headline: 3 Reasons CBRE is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since January 2021, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 82.9%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, CBRE has surged 171% to $164.40 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 15.3% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 5.3%.
